node.text:
On the stunning east coast of Australia is this divine, private eco home - beautifully created, divinely inspired and perfectly peaceful -
surrounded by golden beaches, crystal clear oceans, pure, clean air, and untouched wilderness...
For more info visit www.forsalemilton.com 
Designed and built by @greendraft_design
Video by @gccvisuals

#nswsouthcoast #australia #designer #builder #dreamhome #architecturedaily #residentialdesign #style #beautifulinteriors #luxuryhomes

node.text:
The Nærum suburban #district of #Copenhagen, in #Denmark, is #home to one of the most visually appealing allotment #gardens in the world – the “round gardens”, which are actually #oval.
Carl Theodor Sørensen is considered one of the greatest #landscape #architects to have ever lived, and the oval gardens of #Naerum are one of his most famous projects. 

In 1948, 40 oval allotment gardens, each measuring approximately 25 × 15 m, were laid out on a rolling #lawn, between public housing on one side and more #traditional allotments on the other. Owners were free to position their #cottages, select the surrounding hedges, and lay out the #interior of their plots, but Sørensen provided some directions, stressing that they were meant as a guide, not rules. Seven decades later, the oval gardens of Naerum are still one of the most #beautiful attractions in the Danish capital.

One of the most impressive things about his #design is that the oval gardens look #amazing from above, and even more so from the ground, as you walk amongst them. That was actually the landscape architect’s plan all along.
The lack of road access to each plot may seem like a flaw at first glance, but it’s by design. The architect wanted to encourage owners to walk more, get some fresh air before getting into their cars, as well as greet and maybe socialize with their #neighbors more. Walking among the oval gardens helped them do just that. 📸: @copenhagenbycosedis

Via @fatstudios

#luxclusivehouse

node.text:
How’d you rate this place from 1-10 and why? 💚

The Ex Richaud Factory House is a Colonial factory building that has been transformed to sustain a contemporary lifestyle. The proposal contemplates recovering and restoring the preexisting Colonial structure and giving it a new purpose. The original layout of the colonial house is maintained and the original masonry walls are uncovered to emphasize the age of the property.
The transformation was designed by @richaudarquitectura and the house is located in Campeche, Mexico
Photos by @manolorsolis_fotografia.
Via @restless.arch

#luxclusivehouse
